    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 1,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "RLHF and instruction tuning flatten LLM narrative styles, causing predictable tropes and repetitive vocabulary across models like GPT-4 and Claude.",
        "Standard decoding methods (temperature, top-p) struggle to balance coherence with the high-entropy unpredictability required for engaging, non-formulaic creative writing.",
        "AI fiction exhibits structural idiosyncrasies like rapid resolution, flat character arcs, and a systematic bias toward optimistic, moralistic endings."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Tools or techniques for conveying mental models?",
      "url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ubl3i2",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ubl3i2",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "mw",
      "published": "2026-07-02T14:04:10Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Exhaustive feature-catalog documentation fails to convey system mental models; engineers require interactive, experiential learning to grasp complex architectures.",
        "Hands-on building, direct API usage, and informal whiteboarding are highly effective techniques for rapidly transferring technical mental models.",
        "Intuitive developer tool design and well-architected interfaces naturally teach system behavior better than static, text-heavy documentation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Preventing token theft",
      "url": "https://codon.org.uk/~mjg59/blog/p/preventing-token-theft/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/agwtde",
      "score": 5,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "Foxboron",
      "published": "2026-07-02T11:02:59Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Implement OAuth 2.0 DPoP (RFC 9449) or mTLS to bind tokens to sender keys, neutralizing stolen token replay attacks.",
        "Store session tokens in HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite cookies instead of localStorage to mitigate XSS-based token exfiltration.",
        "Enforce short token lifespans, implement refresh token rotation, and monitor for IP or device fingerprint mismatches during validation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "OpenFeature - Standardizing Feature Flagging for Everyone",
      "url": "https://openfeature.dev/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/4ttyrk",
      "score": 3,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "datboi",
      "published": "2026-07-02T02:31:35Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CNCF-incubating OpenFeature provides a standardized, vendor-agnostic API and SDK ecosystem to unify feature flagging across diverse runtimes.",
        "Decouples application code from specific SaaS backends like LaunchDarkly, Split, or Flagsmith, mitigating proprietary vendor lock-in risks.",
        "Enables DevOps teams to integrate flag evaluations with cloud-native monitoring tools via OpenTelemetry and standardized Kubernetes operators."
      ]
    },
